# License

CCEM (Client Center for Endpoint Manager) uses a dual licensing structure to respect the original work from the SCCMCliCtr project while allowing new contributions under the MIT license.

## Summary

- **All code in this repository not listed below**: MIT License (see `LICENSE_MIT.txt`)
- **Third-party code and derived works**: See `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md` for individual licenses
  - **SCCMCliCtr-derived code** (`src/CCEM/SCCM/Automation/`): Microsoft Public License (Ms-PL) - see `LICENSE_Ms-PL.txt`

---

## Dual License Structure

### 1. MIT License

**Applies to:**
All content in this repository, excluding:
- Code derived from third-party projects (documented in `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md`)
- External dependencies and libraries

**Copyright:** © 2025 Mickaël CHAVE

**Full license text:** See `LICENSE_MIT.txt`

---

### 2. Microsoft Public License (Ms-PL) - Derived Code from SCCMCliCtr

**Applies to:**
- SCCM Automation Library (`src/CCEM/SCCM/Automation/`)
- Code migrated from the original SCCMCliCtr project by Roger Zander

**Original project:** [rzander/sccmclictr](https://github.com/rzander/sccmclictr)

**Original copyright:** © 2018 Roger Zander

**Full license text:** See `LICENSE_Ms-PL.txt`

**Important note:** The original SCCMCliCtr project contains an inconsistency between its LICENSE.md file (Ms-PL) and source code headers (LGPL v3+). We have chosen to respect the Ms-PL license as declared in the official GitHub repository LICENSE file.

